FBIS3-21793 "jptdd011__l94005" JPRS-TDD-94-011-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 14 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA BOLIVIA Former President Garcia Meza Arrested in Sao Paulo PY1103164594 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in Portuguese 1600 GMT 11 Mar 94 PY1103164594 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] The Federal Police arrested former Bolivian President Luis Garcia Meza in Sao Paulo this morning. The former president was hiding in an apartment located in a neighborhood close to the airport and carried a false Brazilian passport. He was taken into custody together with his aide-de-camp, Colonel Roberto Rico. Both of them had been charged with being implicated in an international drug trafficking network. Garcia Meza had been sentenced to 30 years' imprisonment and was a fugitive from Bolivian justice.
